cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper proposes a novel training method for GANs to alleviate the mode collapse phenomenon caused by gradient exploding. The paper focuses on the practical training process of GANs and provides theoretical analysis to support the proposed method. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper also involves the use of difference penalization and fake-as-real consideration, which are related to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the generated distribution, which is related to the sub-category of cs.GR (Graphics).
